        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 6:14PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 614 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles north of Black Forest, or 22 miles north of Colorado Springs,
moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Northeastern Colorado Springs, Calhan, Black Forest, Peyton, Falcon,
and Cimarron Hills.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
